  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 3 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8 - \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "School only 3 days a week - Ministry of Education",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Following the fuel shortage in the country, the Ministry of Education has decided to conduct schools only 3 days a week from next Monday (25) until further notice.",
        "Accordingly, it has been informed that only on 3 days, Monday, Tuesday and Thursday, schools will be held on regular basis.",
        "Along with this, the Ministry of Education has also stated that on Wednesdays and Fridays when schools are not held, students should be taught from home or taught on the Internet."
      ],
